author: democratandchronicle.com
title: City mans pleads to sex trafficking a minor
text:
A Rochester man pleaded guilty to sex trafficking of a minor Wednesday in federal court. Brandon McNeal, 24, was charged by a criminal complaint and faces a minimum of 10 years in prison, a maximum of life in prison, and a $1,000,000 fine.
According to the criminal complaint, McNeal allegedly advertised the services of a 14-year-old on the website Backpages.com. That led to the minor committing commercial sex acts.
McNeal appeared before U.S. Magistrate Judge Marian Payson for a detention hearing on Wednesday. He was released and will return to court on Nov. 17 for a status conference.
WCLEVELAND@Gannett.com
